glory box
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:A chest in which a woman stores linen, clothes, etc. against the time when she will be setting up her own household, or various treasured things. The contents of

such a chest. Cf US hope chest.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1900 at least: common among women, and such chests advertised in furniture shops under the name glory boxes: (WHB Orsman - before WW1 at least check newspaper advts]
